Write a program to check whether the given three sides of a triangle are valid or not.


a = float(input("Enter the length of the first side: "))
b = float(input("Enter the length of the second side: "))
c = float(input("Enter the length of the third side: "))


max_side = max(a, b, c)


if a + b > max_side and a + c > max_side and b + c > max_side:
   print("The given sides can form a valid triangle.")
else:
   print("The given sides cannot form a valid triangle.")



